Description: Ostracon, fragment from the body of a pale-red pottery wine-jar, interior grooved and exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip, with remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text specifying contents as year 14 wine of the Aten domain from the western river.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389864) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389864)
